<exercise checkit-seed="0013" checkit-slug="V8" checkit-title="Polynomial and matrix spaces">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the statement
        <claim> The set of polynomials <m> \left\{ -4 \, x^{3} - 6 \, x^{2} + 5 \, x - 3 , -6 \, x^{3} + x^{2} - x - 5 , 4 \, x^{3} - 5 \, x^{2} + x - 1 , 16 \, x^{3} - 7 \, x^{2} + 3 \, x + 9 \right\} </m> is linearly independent.</claim></p>
    <ol>
      <li> Write an equivalent statement using a polynomial equation.</li>
      <li> Explain why your statement is true or false.</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>
      <me>\operatorname{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-3 &amp; -5 &amp; -1 &amp; 9 \\
5 &amp; -1 &amp; 1 &amp; 3 \\
-6 &amp; 1 &amp; -5 &amp; -7 \\
-4 &amp; -6 &amp; 4 &amp; 16
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>The statement
            <claim> The set of polynomials <m> \left\{ -4 \, x^{3} - 6 \, x^{2} + 5 \, x - 3 , -6 \, x^{3} + x^{2} - x - 5 , 4 \, x^{3} - 5 \, x^{2} + x - 1 , 16 \, x^{3} - 7 \, x^{2} + 3 \, x + 9 \right\} </m> is linearly independent.</claim>
            is equivalent to the statement
            <claim>
                    The polynomial  equation 
                    <me> y_{1} \left( -4 \, x^{3} - 6 \, x^{2} + 5 \, x - 3 \right) + y_{2} \left( -6 \, x^{3} + x^{2} - x - 5 \right) + y_{3} \left( 4 \, x^{3} - 5 \, x^{2} + x - 1 \right) + y_{4} \left( 16 \, x^{3} - 7 \, x^{2} + 3 \, x + 9 \right) = 0 </me>
                    has no nontrivial solutions.
                </claim></li>
      <li>The set of polynomials <m> \left\{ -4 \, x^{3} - 6 \, x^{2} + 5 \, x - 3 , -6 \, x^{3} + x^{2} - x - 5 , 4 \, x^{3} - 5 \, x^{2} + x - 1 , 16 \, x^{3} - 7 \, x^{2} + 3 \, x + 9 \right\} </m>is linearly dependent.</li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

